  "summary": "Yuzu informs the detective that she saw her Uncle Aoba walking toward her brother Kei's room after midnight the previous night. Although the corridor was dark and she only saw his profile, she is certain it was him. The detective expresses disbelief, noting that Inaba is dead and questioning the timing of such a sighting. Yuzu expresses guilt, wondering if she could have saved her brother if she had checked his room sooner.\n\nMeanwhile, Wanli Hua presents an ancient, fragile book to Mutou, which she found inside a table at a church. The book is bound with ropes, features torn pages, and contains text in both Latin and English. Mutou identifies the volume as the \"Lecanova Book,\" an apocryphal gospel of the New Testament that focuses on the humanity of Jesus during his crucifixion. \n\nFollowing this discovery, Kanae notes that the book is similar to one her grandfather used to carry when visiting a \"jail\" (which Kanade suggests may be the \"gate of hell\"). Kanae describes her grandfather wearing a black cloak and carrying a strange tree branch, appearing to perform a secret ritual. Xiao Yan reflects on the possibility that Itou, who was the first victim, might be the murderer using a scapegoat, or that the killer utilized the discovered book. Mutou and Kaneko depart to investigate further, acknowledging that new facts are emerging.",
